00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:14.700
Tomato Focaccia

00:00:14.700 --> 00:00:17.000
Serves: 6-8

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:19.900
Ingredients for the dough:

00:00:19.900 --> 00:00:23.200
500 g (3½ cups) bread flour

00:00:23.200 --> 00:00:26.600
300 ml (1¼ cups) warm water

00:00:26.600 --> 00:00:32.100
7g (about 2 tsp) active dry yeast 

00:00:32.100 --> 00:00:35.900
2 tbsp Serjella Extra Virgin Olive Oil

00:00:35.900 --> 00:00:38.300
1 tsp brown sugar

00:00:38.300 --> 00:00:40.300
1 tsp salt

00:00:40.300 --> 00:00:42.300
Ingredients for the topping: 

00:00:42.300 --> 00:00:45.400
Serjella Extra Virgin Olive Oil olive oil

00:00:45.400 --> 00:00:49.900
300 g (2 cups) cherry tomatoes, halved

00:00:49.900 --> 00:00:52.800
1 tbsp dried oregano

00:00:52.800 --> 00:00:54.700
Sea salt

00:00:54.700 --> 00:00:56.200
Directions

00:00:56.200 --> 00:01:04.700
Sieve the flour and salt together into a large bowl and make a well in the centre.

00:01:04.700 --> 00:01:13.500
Dissolve the yeast and sugar in the 300 ml of water, wait a few minutes until it becomes foamy

00:01:13.500 --> 00:01:23.500
then add the olive oil and pour the mixture into the well.

00:01:23.500 --> 00:01:39.500
Bring together with your fingers until it forms a ball and start kneading the dough until smooth.

00:01:39.500 --> 00:01:43.900
Brush the dough with olive oil, put it back into the bowl

00:01:43.900 --> 00:01:50.400
cover it with a kitchen towel and let it rest for 1 hour at room temperature.

00:01:50.400 --> 00:01:59.000
Place the dough over parchment paper and roll it out into a circle or rectangle of 2.5 cm thick. 

00:01:59.000 --> 00:02:05.900
Cover with a kitchen cloth and let it rise again for 1 hour.

00:02:05.900 --> 00:02:09.000
Meanwhile, put the tomatoes in a bowl

00:02:09.000 --> 00:02:23.900
drizzle 2 tablespoons of olive oil and 1 tbsp of dried oregano and toss to coat.

00:02:23.900 --> 00:02:31.900
When the dough is ready, press all over with your fingers to make little wells that will retain the flavourings.

00:02:31.900 --> 00:02:40.900
Brush the dough with olive oil, spread the tomatoes over the top and sprinkle some sea salt

00:02:40.900 --> 00:02:48.200
then bake the focaccia for 20-25 minutes in a preheated oven at 200°C.

00:02:48.200 --> 00:02:56.000
As soon as you take the focaccia out of the oven drizzle with more olive oil.

